# === Root whitelist (ignore-everything, then re-allow) ===
# Agents run their tooling in this repo and routinely drop stray files at the
# root — screenshots, scratch output, debug dumps, root-level package.json /
# pnpm-lock.yaml from running pnpm in the wrong place. The auto-merge gate
# rejects any PR that touches a path outside ONE projects/<slug>/ folder, so a
# single stray root file silently blocks an otherwise-valid project PR (see
# PR #73). So: ignore everything at the root, then re-allow only the known-good
# entries below. Stray root files become un-committable by default. Add a new
# root path here only on purpose.
/*
!/.github/
!/.gitignore
!/.nojekyll
!/AGENTS.md
!/CLAUDE.md
!/LICENSE
!/README.md
!/assets/
!/index.html
!/projects/
!/scripts/

# === Below the root ===
# The whitelist above only governs top-level entries; these still apply inside
# projects/<slug>/ and any other subdirectory.
node_modules/
projects/*/dist/
*.log
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db
